1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,890
We can't do much to change the amount of native ability, but we can certainly change the way we use what we have.

2
00:00:09,919 --> 00:00:13,729
Knowledge is power when you use it constructively.

3
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:20,689
Closely allied to intelligence excusitis is some incorrect thinking about knowledge.

4
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:26,449
We often hear that knowledge is power, but this statement is only a half-truth.

5
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,330
Knowledge is only potential power.

6
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:36,530
Knowledge is power only when put to use, and then only when the use made of it is constructive.

7
00:00:37,199 --> 00:00:44,050
The story is told that the great scientist Einstein was once asked how many feet are in a mile.

8
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:47,410
Einstein's reply was, I don't know.

9
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:53,729
Why should I fill my brain with facts I can find in two minutes in any standard reference book?

10
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,770
Einstein taught us a big lesson.

11
00:00:57,040 --> 00:01:03,330
He felt it was more important to use your mind to think than to use it as a warehouse for facts.

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,929
One time Henry Ford was involved in a libel suit with the Chicago Tribune.

13
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:15,169
The Tribune had called Ford an ignoramus, and Ford said, in effect, prove it.

14
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:21,570
The Tribune asked him scores of simple questions, such as who was Benedict Arnold,

15
00:01:21,679 --> 00:01:28,209
when was the Revolutionary War fought, and others, most of which Ford, who had little formal education,

16
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:29,489
could not answer.

17
00:01:29,919 --> 00:01:36,370
Finally, he became quite exasperated and said, I don't know the answers to those questions,

18
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:39,650
but I could find a man in five minutes who does.

19
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:44,610
Henry Ford was never interested in miscellaneous information.

20
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:55,330
He knew what every major executive knows, that the ability to know how to get information is more important than using the mind as a garage for facts.

21
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:59,010
How much is a fact man worth?

